  <channel>
    <title>Refugees contributor: Geoff Gilbert</title>
    <description>Geoff Gilbert is a professor of law at the School of Law and Human Rights Centre at the University of Essex. In 2012, he was appointed a visiting professorial fellow at UNSW Sydney. He was editor-in-chief of the International Journal of Refugee Law from 2002–15 and now sits on its editorial board. In 2014 he was appointed as a consultant to the United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) (with Anna Magdalena Rusch) on Rule of Law: Engagement for Solutions, and is part of the Solutions Alliance Thematic Group on Rule of Law. Their coauthored report has helped to shape UNHCR’s approach to protracted displacement. He has published widely on international refugee law and international criminal law.
</description>
